{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01R3tM1XsXT2toKATfdhNuLq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The jq works fine in a subshell. So the issue is specifically with the function definition when sourced via `bash -c`. Let me test the exact function again.\n\nActually wait - let me look at the `cc_extract_text` function again more carefully:\n\n```bash\ncc_extract_text() {\n    local log_file=\"$1\"\n    local max_chars=\"${2:-500}\"\n\n    [[ -f \"$log_file\" ]] || { echo \"\"; return; }\n    [[ -s \"$log_file\" ]] || { echo \"\"; return; }\n\n    # Detect format: stream-json starts with '{'\n\n\n```\n\nNow I'm checking the first character of the log file to determine if it's in Claude's stream-json format, then using jq to extract either the result or assistant message content...\n\nExtracting text from jq... I'm realizing the `set -euo pipefail` in `lib.sh` might be causing the function to fail silently, and suppressing jq's stderr with `2>/dev/null` could be masking the actual error. I should test the function more carefully to see what `first_char` actually returns and whether jq is executing properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":701,"cache_read_input_tokens":68650,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":701},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7dec3f60-2165-4422-8434-2be6f8f9065a","uuid":"0a6ef808-b9ea-46ed-8737-2e719b84722b"}
