{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019vmu68UtTsn5Fes8nWfNfa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Very interesting! The jq works fine directly (returns \"Fixed the bug!\") but the function call returns empty. The function must have an issue. Let me look at it more carefully.\n\nThe function `cc_extract_text` in lib.sh has this specific part:\n\n```bash\n    if [[ \"$first_char\" == \"{\" ]]; then\n        # Claude stream-json format\n        local text\n        text=$(jq -rs '\n          ([ .[] | select(.type == \"result\") | (.result // \"\") ] | last // \"\") as $result |\n          ([ .[] | select(.type == \"assistant\") |\n             ((.message.content // []) | map(select(.type == \"text\") | .text) | join(\"\"))\n          ] | last // \"\") as $assistant |\n          ([ .[] |\n             select(.type == \"stream_event\") |\n             select(.event.type == \"content_block_delta\") |\n             select(.event.delta.type == \"text_delta\") |\n             .event.delta.text\n          ] | join(\"\")) as $delta |\n          if $result != \"\" then $result\n          elif $assistant != \"\" then $assistant\n          elif $delta != \"\" then $delta\n          else \"\"\n          end\n        ' \"$log_\n```\n\nThe jq filter is extracting text from multiple possible locations in the JSON structure—checking for result fields, assistant message content, and stream event deltas—then returning whichever one has content. Still writing the filter... I wonder if the jq filter in the actual function differs from what I tested in isolation—maybe the three-branch version with `text_delta` has a syntax error that the simpler two-branch version didn't catch. Let me run the full filter to see if that's where the problem is.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":529,"cache_read_input_tokens":70315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":529},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7dec3f60-2165-4422-8434-2be6f8f9065a","uuid":"d47b9303-9a50-4744-a6ce-fe5cfceb24a4"}
